Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da "ta'addanci" da "tallace-tallacen farfaganda"
Jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka a matsayin kayan aikin farfaganda, wannan na zuwa ne mako guda bayan da wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wata takarda mai shafi hudu a cikin wani jaridar Amurka, tana mai yabon amfanin yarjejeniyar cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da Sin.
A ranar Laraba, shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi tsokaci kan wani karin da China Daily ta biya a jaridar Des Moines Register, wadda ita ce jaridar da ta fi kowanne girma a Iowa, inda ta zargi China da hannu a zaben da za a yi a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba.
Masu magana da Reuters sun ce zargin da Trump ya yi wa Beijing na son tsoma baki a zaben Amurka, wani sabon mataki ne a wani gagarumin yunkurin da Washington ke yi na matsa wa China lamba.
Duk da cewa ba sabon abu ba ne ga wata gwamnati ta kasashen waje ta yada wasu tallace-tallace don bunkasa kasuwanci, a yanzu haka Beijing da Washington sun shiga cikin wani rikici na cinikayya da ke taɓarɓarewa, inda kowannensu ke ba da haraji a kan kayayyakin da ake fitarwa daga wata ƙasa.
Masana a Sin da Amurka sun ce a farkon yakin cinikayya, kasar Sin ta yi amfani da takunkumi don ramuwar gayya ga jihohin da suka goyi bayan Trump a lokacin da yake takara, kamar Iowa.
Terry Branstad, tsohon jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan jihar Iowa, ya ce, abin da Beijing ta yi, ya yi wa ma'aikata, manoma da kamfanonin Amurka illa.
"A yanzu haka, China za ta kara daukaka ta hanyar wallafa labaran farfaganda a jaridarmu mai 'yanci", in ji Branstad a cikin wata sanarwa da aka wallafa a jaridar Des Moines Register a ranar Lahadi.
"Ta hanyar yada farfaganda, gwamnatin China ta ci gajiyar al'adun Amurka na 'yancin magana da 'yan jarida ta hanyar sanya talla da aka biya a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A bangaren 'yan jarida a titunan birnin Beijing, ana iya ganin bambancin ra'ayi a takaice, kuma ba a ga bambancin ra'ayi da 'yan kasar Sin za su iya samu game da ci gaban tattalin arzikin kasar ba, saboda kafofin watsa labarai sun yi aiki a karkashin jagorancin jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
Branstad ya kara da cewa, "daya daga cikin manyan jaridun kasar Sin ya ki amincewa da buga wata kasida da ya rubuta, amma bai bayyana takamaiman jaridar ba".
Masu sharhi sun ce, "Rashin nasarar Kavanaugh zai sa mata masu jefa kuri'a su yi watsi da 'yan Republican".
